                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d570">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.24546/6: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul at Nouméa</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacVitty</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-10-29T23:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 29, 1941—11 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>20. Your 22, October 22, 10 a.m. Department approves your action in not
                    presenting matter to High Commissioner in view of circumstances described. The
                    War Department has instructed the Commanding General at Hawaii<note n="13"
                        xml:id="d570fn13">Gen. Walter Campbell Short.</note> to communicate with the
                    Australians with reference to bases in New Caledonia.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
